 At Hooli, new hires receive RSU grants that need to be converted to U.S. dollars before determining the actual number of shares. This conversion uses the 9-month average exchange rate up to the first business day of the Hooli fiscal quarter, which corresponds to the start date of employment. For instance, a new hire starting May 2, 2022, with a grant target value of €200,000 would convert it to approximately 1,300 RSUs, assuming the 21-working day average stock price was $177.91 and the exchange rate was 0.864594. These RSUs are typically granted on the eleventh business day of the month following their start date. They become visible in the employee's Schwab account during the second week of the subsequent month. To see the vesting schedule, employees must log into their personal investor portal after one year of service.

